						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. IV) set up in the Basavēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Harihara I A.D. 1349.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription referring itself to the reign of Harihara I is dated Śaka [1271] Sarvadhāri, Phālguna śu. 1, Thursday. (A.D. 1349, February 19).</p>						

						<p>It records the death of a warrior in a fight (detail not clear) when the king's officer Samudra-saḷuva Vīra-Bāchappadēva was administering the tract.</p>						

						</summary>
